p: Qualitative analysis of the EOs marjoram, tea tree, rosewood and lemongrass, enabled the detection of 55 different components that had relative abundances greater than 10% and / or were flagged by the instrument ( S3, S4, S5 and S6 Tables). The principal components for each oil were identified as follows: marjoram, eucalyptol; tea tree, terpinen-4-ol; rosewood, linalool; lemongrass, Î±-citral. Similarity index (SI) and reverse similarity index (RSI) mass spectral match factors for all the compounds except dihydrolinalool were above 800, allowing good identification of compounds.
